{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MWpKYZvqRNRSqqUGYDJFJX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Add comment delete button to theme detail page\n     2→\n     3→## Context\n     4→The `comments.remove` mutation already exists in `app/convex/comments.ts` (line 76) and handles auth checks (only the comment author can delete their own comment). However, the theme detail page (`app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`) has no UI to trigger this mutation. Users can post comments but can never delete them. This is an incomplete feature that needs to be rounded out for MVP.\n     5→\n     6→Also fix a minor bug: the API usage reference on the theme detail page shows `/api/theme/{slug}` (line 519) but the correct Convex HTTP endpoint pattern should match whatever is actually deployed. Verify and correct if needed.\n     7→\n     8→## Scope\n     9→Add a delete button to each comment in the theme detail page, visible only to the comment's author. Wire it to the existing `comments.remove` mutation. Small, focused change in a single file.\n    10→\n    11→## Tasks\n    12→\n    13→### 1. Wire up the `comments.remove` mutation\n    14→- **File:** `app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`\n    15→- Add `useMutation(api.comments.remove)` alongside the existing comment mutations\n    16→- Add a handler function that calls remove with the comment `_id` and includes a confirmation prompt\n    17→\n    18→### 2. Add delete button to comment UI\n    19→- **File:** `app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx` (around lines 690-714)\n    20→- In each comment's rendered div, add a small delete button (trash icon or \"Delete\" text)\n    21→- Only show the button when `currentUser?._id === comment.userId`\n    22→- The comment list query returns `comment.userId` (the raw field from the comments table) which can be compared against the current user's `_id`\n    23→- Style consistently with the existing UI (small, subtle, hover to reveal or always visible but muted)\n    24→\n    25→### 3. Handle delete state\n    26→- Show a loading/disabled state while the delete is in progress\n    27→- Optimistic UI is not needed since Convex queries auto-update reactively\n    28→\n    29→## Acceptance criteria\n    30→- [ ] Each comment shows a delete button only to the comment's author\n    31→- [ ] Clicking delete prompts for confirmation (\"Delete this comment?\")\n    32→- [ ] After confirming, the comment is removed and the list updates reactively\n    33→- [ ] Delete button is styled consistently with the page (subtle, not visually heavy)\n    34→- [ ] No new npm dependencies required\n    35→- [ ] TypeScript compiles cleanly\n    36→\n    37→## Technical notes\n    38→- The `comments.remove` mutation (`app/convex/comments.ts:76`) takes `{ id: v.id(\"comments\") }` and checks that `comment.userId === user._id` server-side\n    39→- The `listByTheme` query already returns `comment._id` and `comment.userId` on each comment object\n    40→- The current user object is already fetched in the page component as `currentUser`\n    41→- Convex reactive queries will automatically refresh the comment list after deletion — no manual refetch needed\n    42→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d8cbb2b-c1a2-4d55-970a-911c604b3f71","uuid":"7be3ad59-5e52-4f2b-ba4f-19922ca6e530","timestamp":"2026-03-28T00:17:10.804Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/matt/code/themedrops/swarm/tasks/comment-delete-ui.todo.md","content":"# Add comment delete button to theme detail page\n\n## Context\nThe `comments.remove` mutation already exists in `app/convex/comments.ts` (line 76) and handles auth checks (only the comment author can delete their own comment). However, the theme detail page (`app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`) has no UI to trigger this mutation. Users can post comments but can never delete them. This is an incomplete feature that needs to be rounded out for MVP.\n\nAlso fix a minor bug: the API usage reference on the theme detail page shows `/api/theme/{slug}` (line 519) but the correct Convex HTTP endpoint pattern should match whatever is actually deployed. Verify and correct if needed.\n\n## Scope\nAdd a delete button to each comment in the theme detail page, visible only to the comment's author. Wire it to the existing `comments.remove` mutation. Small, focused change in a single file.\n\n## Tasks\n\n### 1. Wire up the `comments.remove` mutation\n- **File:** `app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`\n- Add `useMutation(api.comments.remove)` alongside the existing comment mutations\n- Add a handler function that calls remove with the comment `_id` and includes a confirmation prompt\n\n### 2. Add delete button to comment UI\n- **File:** `app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx` (around lines 690-714)\n- In each comment's rendered div, add a small delete button (trash icon or \"Delete\" text)\n- Only show the button when `currentUser?._id === comment.userId`\n- The comment list query returns `comment.userId` (the raw field from the comments table) which can be compared against the current user's `_id`\n- Style consistently with the existing UI (small, subtle, hover to reveal or always visible but muted)\n\n### 3. Handle delete state\n- Show a loading/disabled state while the delete is in progress\n- Optimistic UI is not needed since Convex queries auto-update reactively\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Each comment shows a delete button only to the comment's author\n- [ ] Clicking delete prompts for confirmation (\"Delete this comment?\")\n- [ ] After confirming, the comment is removed and the list updates reactively\n- [ ] Delete button is styled consistently with the page (subtle, not visually heavy)\n- [ ] No new npm dependencies required\n- [ ] TypeScript compiles cleanly\n\n## Technical notes\n- The `comments.remove` mutation (`app/convex/comments.ts:76`) takes `{ id: v.id(\"comments\") }` and checks that `comment.userId === user._id` server-side\n- The `listByTheme` query already returns `comment._id` and `comment.userId` on each comment object\n- The current user object is already fetched in the page component as `currentUser`\n- Convex reactive queries will automatically refresh the comment list after deletion — no manual refetch needed\n","numLines":42,"startLine":1,"totalLines":42}}}
